This paper discusses the application of machine learning and natural language processing to extract ethical and moral values from text, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of BERT, a popular language model in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and its impact on improving the representation of ethical and moral values in machines. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the moral compass of machines, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential applications of this research in robotics (cs.RO) and cybersecurity (cs.CY), which are relevant sub-categories given the potential implications of machines with a moral compass.
